        "role": "assistant",
        "content": "{\"type\":\"code\",\"content\":\"Create a comprehensive README.md for the ESP32-S3 soil moisture monitoring system (polivator). Include the following sections:\\n\\n1. **Project Overview** — ESP32-S3-based soil moisture monitor with capacitive sensor, e-ink display, web server for phone access, and calibration system. Designed to be extended into a full auto-watering system.\\n\\n2. **Hardware Requirements**\\n   - ESP32-S3 (WROOM-1)\\n   - WeActStudio 2.13\\\" e-ink display (SPI)\\n   - Capacitive soil moisture sensor v1.2\\n   - Jumper wires, breadboard\\n   - Power: USB 5V or battery (mention power consumption considerations)\\n\\n3. **Pin Connections** — Include a table:\\n   | ESP32 Pin | Component |\\n   |-----------|-----------|\\n   | GPIO4     | Moisture sensor analog output |\\n   | GPIO10    | E-ink CS |\\n   | GPIO9     | E-ink DC |\\n   | GPIO8     | E-ink RST |\\n   | GPIO7     | E-ink BUSY |\\n   | GPIO11    | E-ink MOSI (DIN) |\\n   | GPIO12    | E-ink SCK (CLK) |\\n   | 3V3/VIN   | Sensor VCC |\\n   | GND       | Common ground |\\n\\n4. **Software Setup**\\n   - Install PlatformIO in VS Code\\n   - Clone repository\\n   - Install dependencies (list: GxEPD2, ESPAsyncWebServer, AsyncTCP, ArduinoJson)\\n   - Build and upload to ESP32-S3\\n   - PlatformIO environment: `env:esp32dev` with custom board options for S3\\n\\n5. **First Run / WiFi Configuration**\\n   - Device starts in Access Point mode with SSID \\\"PlantMonitor\\\"\\n   - Connect phone/PC to that WiFi, open 192.168.4.1 in browser\\n   - Use WiFi configuration page (captive portal) to enter home WiFi credentials\\n   - Device reboots and connects to home network; note its IP (shown on display)\\n\\n6. **Web Interface Usage**\\n   - Open the device IP in a browser\\n   - Real-time moisture gauge (dashboard)\\n   - Raw ADC value, voltage, dry/wet thresholds, WiFi status\\n   - Line chart of moisture over time (last 60 readings)\\n   - Calibration buttons: Dry, Wet, Reset\\n\\n7. **Calibration**\\n   - **Dry calibration**: Insert sensor into dry air / dry soil, press \\\"Calibrate Dry\\\" (or send 'd' via serial). Sets current raw value as dry threshold.\\n   - **Wet calibration**: Insert sensor into a glass of water (or fully wet soil), press \\\"Calibrate Wet\\\" (or 'w'). Sets current raw value as wet threshold.\\n   - **Reset**: Resets to default thresholds (3000 dry, 1200 wet).\\n   - Thresholds stored in NVS (non-volatile storage).\\n\\n8. **Serial Commands**\\n   - 'd' — set dry threshold\\n   - 'w' — set wet threshold\\n   - 'r' — reset calibration\\n   - Must have calibration mode active (instruction to send 'c'? Actually code uses 'c' to enable calibration? Need to check. From code: in Serial, after 'c' enters calibration mode. Document that first send 'c' to enter calibration mode, then 'd','w','r'.\\n\\n9. **API Reference**\\n   - `GET /api/status` — JSON with moisture, raw, voltage, dry, wet, wifi\\n   - `POST /api/calibrate/dry` — set dry threshold\\n   - `POST /api/calibrate/wet` — set wet threshold\\n   - `POST /api/calibrate/reset` — reset thresholds\\n   - `GET /events` — Server-Sent Events with live updates\\n\\n10. **Project Structure**\\n    ```\\n    polivator/\\n    ├── platformio.ini\\n    ├── src/\\n    │   └── main.cpp           # Main firmware, initialisation and loop\\n    ├── lib/\\n    │   ├── Sensor/\\n    │   │   ├── Sensor.h       # Capacitive moisture sensor class\\n    │   │   └── Sensor.cpp\\n    │   ├── Calibration/\\n    │   │   ├── Calibration.h   # Calibration thresholds with NVS storage\\n    │   │   └── Calibration.cpp\\n    │   ├── Display/\\n    │   │   ├── Display.h       # E-ink display driver (WeAct 2.13\\\")\\n    │   │   └── Display.cpp\\n    │   └── WebServer/\\n    │       ├── WebServer.h     # HTTP server with REST API and SSE\\n    │       ├── WebServer.cpp\\n    │       └── index.h         # Web UI as C++ string\\n    └── README.md\\n    ```\\n\\n11. **Extending to Auto-Watering**\\n    - Add a relay/valve controlled by a GPIO\\n    - Add a water level sensor (optional)\\n    - Implement PID or threshold-based watering logic in main loop\\n    - Add scheduling (time-controlled watering) via web UI\\n    - Use FreeRTOS tasks for concurrent operations\\n\\n12. **Troubleshooting**\\n    - Display not working: check SPI wiring (CS, DC, RST, BUSY, MOSI, SCK)\\n    - Sensor reads 4095 always: check analog pin connection, ensure ADC attenuation is set\\n    - Web UI not loading: check WiFi connection, serial monitor for IP\\n    - Calibration not saving: NVS may be full; erase with `idf.py erase-flash` (or PlatformIO erase)\\n\\n13. **License** — MIT or whatever applies\\n\\nUse proper Markdown formatting: headings, tables, code blocks, lists.\\n\\nWrite to file `README.md` in the root of the project.\",\"role\":\"docs\",\"skills\":[\"documentation\"],\"params\":{\"files\":\"README.md\"},\"_toolId\":\"tool-1781434362017\"}"
