        "content": "Code agent result:\nSummary: The display update cycle is driven by two timers in the main loop: sensor reading every 2 seconds (via sensorManager.readAll() and SSE event) and display refresh every 10 seconds. The display refresh function (inside the 10‑second timer) checks if 'calibrating' is true: if so, it calls display.showCalibrationScreen() (full window refresh). Otherwise, it collects current sensor data (percent, raw) and WiFi status, then calls display.showStatus(). showStatus() uses a partial window update but performs a full redraw if data changed or if m_firstUpdate is true (set by forceFullRefresh(), showCalibrationScreen(), or showMessage()). The forceFullRefresh() method is called by web server endpoints for enabling/disabling sensors, forcing the next showStatus() to redraw regardless of changes. showMessage() and showCalibrationScreen() always use full window refresh and set m_firstUpdate = true. The main purpose is to display sensor status (name, percentage, raw value) and WiFi state, with occasional overlay messages or calibration screens.\n\nContinue.\n\n[WARNING] The code agent has returned without changes. Ensure your next action makes concrete edits or moves the task forward."
