        "role": "user",
        "content": "Code agent result:\nSummary: ## Summary of Existing Structure\n\n### Settings Storage\n- **Preferences** used in two namespaces:\n  - `\"wifi\"`: Stores WiFi SSID (`ssid`) and password (`pass`) as strings.\n  - `\"calib\"`: Stores sensor configurations as a JSON string (`config`) containing an array of objects with fields: `name`, `dryRaw`, `wetRaw`, `enabled`.\n- Calibration class loads config in `begin()`, saves after every modification via `saveAllConfigs()`.\n- Default sensor config: pin from board wiring, `dryRaw=3000`, `wetRaw=1200`, `enabled=true`, name \"Sensor N\".\n\n### Web Routes (AsyncWebServer on port 80)\n- `GET /` → serves web UI (index.html content)\n- `GET /api/status` → JSON with sensor readings, calibration values, WiFi status\n- `POST /api/calibrate/dry?index=N` → set dry calibration from current raw value\n- `POST /api/calibrate/wet?index=N` → set wet calibration\n- `POST /api/calibrate/reset?index=N` → reset to defaults\n- `POST /api/config/sensor?index=N` → set sensor name (JSON body `{\"name\":...}`)\n- `DELETE /api/sensor?index=N` → disable sensor (calls `removeSensor`)\n- `POST /api/sensor/enable?index=N` → enable sensor\n- `GET /api/calibration` → JSON with all sensor calibration values\n- `GET /wifi` → WiFi configuration HTML page (captive portal)\n- `POST /wifi/connect` → save credentials and reboot\n- `GET /api/wifi` → stored SSID\n- `POST /api/config/wifi` → save credentials via JSON and reboot\n- SSE endpoint `/events` for real-time status updates\n- 404 handler\n\n### Update Logic (main.cpp loop)\n- **Sensor reading**: every 2 seconds (`lastSensorRead`), calls `sensorManager.readAll()` and sends SSE event.\n- **Configuration change detection**: compares previous and current dry/wet values; sets `forceDisplayUpdate` if changed.\n- **Display update**: every 30 seconds OR when `forceDisplayUpdate` is true. During display update, if `calibrating` flag is true, shows calibration screen; otherwise shows sensor status.\n- **Serial commands**: `c` toggles calibration mode, digits 0-4 select sensor\n\nContinue.\n\n[WARNING] The code agent has returned without changes. Ensure your next action makes concrete edits or moves the task forward."
