        "content": "Code agent result:\nSummary: ## WiFi-related Routes\n\n### GET /wifi\n- Serves an HTML page with a form for SSID and password.\n- No JSON, no content-type handling.\n\n### POST /wifi/connect\n- Receives form-urlencoded data (ssid, password) via HTTP POST.\n- Parses using `request->hasParam(\"ssid\", true)` etc.\n- Saves to Preferences and reboots.\n- No JSON parsing.\n\n### GET /api/wifi\n- Returns JSON with current SSID from Preferences.\n- Content-type: application/json.\n\n### POST /api/config/wifi\n- Expects JSON body with fields \"ssid\" (required) and \"pass\" (optional).\n- Checks Content-Type starts with \"application/json\" using `request->contentType().startsWith(\"application/json\")`.\n- Parses JSON using ArduinoJson with `deserializeJson(doc, body)`.\n- If JSON invalid, returns 400.\n- Saves to Preferences and reboots.\n\n### Other Endpoints with Content-Type Handling\n- **POST /api/config/sensor?index=N**: expects JSON with \"name\", checks Content-Type.\n- **POST /api/settings**: expects JSON with \"interval\", \"priority\", checks Content-Type.\n\n## Summary\nWiFi credentials are saved via two endpoints: HTML form and JSON API. The JSON endpoint validates Content-Type and parses ArduinoJson. No other advanced JSON parsing (like nested objects) is used for WiFi.\n\nContinue.\n\n[WARNING] The code agent has returned without changes. Ensure your next action makes concrete edits or moves the task forward."
