        "command": "Implement the Sensor module for capacitive soil moisture sensor.\n\nFile: lib/Sensor/Sensor.h\n- Class Sensor with constructor taking pin number\n- begin() to initialize ADC\n- readRaw() - returns averaged raw ADC value (0-4095)\n- readPercent() - returns moisture percentage (0-100) using calibration data (dry/wet thresholds) - but calibration will be separate, so for now use hardcoded defaults or take thresholds as parameters\n- readVoltage() - returns voltage (0-3.3V)\n- setCalibration(dry, wet) to set thresholds\n- Private: m_pin, m_dryValue, m_wetValue\n- Use ADC1, channel based on pin\n- static const int SAMPLES = 10; // number of samples to average\n- Smoothing: exponential moving average or simple average\n\nFile: lib/Sensor/Sensor.cpp\n- Implement using Arduino analogRead on designated pin\n- Actually ESP32-S3 has two ADCs. Use analogRead(pin) which uses ADC1 by default. Set resolution to 12 bits with analogReadResolution(12). Set attenuation to 11dB with analogSetAttenuation(ADC_11db).\n- In begin(): call analogReadResolution(12); analogSetAttenuation(ADC_11db);\n- In readRaw(): read SAMPLES times, sum, divide, maybe discard outliers? Simple average for now.\n- In readPercent(): map readRaw() between m_dryValue and m_wetValue. If raw <= wet -> 100%; if raw >= dry -> 0%; else map linearly.\n- Default m_dryValue = 3000 (dry air), m_wetValue = 1200 (water) - user must calibrate.\n\nEnsure the code compiles with Arduino framework. Use proper #include guards.",
