        "command": "Implement the Calibration module for storing soil moisture sensor thresholds in NVS (Non-Volatile Storage).\n\nFile: lib/Calibration/Calibration.h\n- Class Calibration\n- begin() - open Preferences with namespace \"calib\", read-only mode on first call? Actually use read-write.\n- getDryValue() -> uint16_t\n- getWetValue() -> uint16_t\n- setDryValue(uint16_t value) - save to NVS\n- setWetValue(uint16_t value) - save to NVS\n- resetToDefaults() - set dry=3000, wet=1200\n- Private: Preferences prefs; constants for keys: \"dry\", \"wet\"\n- Use default values if NVS doesn't have them yet\n\nFile: lib/Calibration/Calibration.cpp\n- Include <Preferences.h>\n- begin(): prefs.begin(\"calib\", false); check if keys exist, if not, set defaults\n- getDryValue(): return prefs.getUShort(\"dry\", 3000);\n- getWetValue(): return prefs.getUShort(\"wet\", 1200);\n- setDryValue(uint16_t v): prefs.putUShort(\"dry\", v);\n- setWetValue(uint16_t v): prefs.putUShort(\"wet\", v);\n- resetToDefaults(): put both defaults\n\nAlso modify Sensor::setCalibration to take uint16_t dry, uint16_t wet (already exists in header). In main, we'll read from Calibration and pass to Sensor.",
