        "command": "Update the project with correct pin assignments based on typical WeActStudio 2.13\" e-ink module wiring for ESP32-S3 (using hardware SPI or flexible GPIO).\n\n**Pinout table (standard for WeAct 2.13\" e-paper with GxEPD2 library):**\n\n| Display pin | GPIO ESP32-S3 |\n|-------------|---------------|\n| BUSY        | 4             |\n| RES         | 16            |\n| D/C         | 17            |\n| CS          | 5             |\n| SCK         | 18            |\n| MOSI(SDA)   | 23            |\n| GND         | GND           |\n| VCC         | 3.3V          |\n\n| Moisture sensor pin | ESP32-S3 |\n|---------------------|----------|\n| AOUT                | GPIO2 (ADC) |\n| VCC                 | 3.3V     |\n| GND                 | GND      |\n\n**Changes needed:**\n\n1. `lib/Display/Display.h` — update pin definitions:\n   - EINK_BUSY = 4\n   - EINK_RST = 16\n   - EINK_DC = 17\n   - EINK_CS = 5\n   - EINK_MOSI = 23\n   - EINK_SCLK = 18\n\n2. `lib/Display/Display.cpp` — after `m_display.init(115200);` add:\n   - `m_display.setMosi(EINK_MOSI);`\n   - `m_display.setSck(EINK_SCLK);`\n   Ensure these methods exist (they do in GxEPD2). If not, alternative: init with SPI parameters.\n\n3. `src/main.cpp` — change sensor pin from 4 to 2:\n   - `Sensor sensor(2);`\n\n4. `README.md` — update both tables with correct pin assignments and add explanation about SPI.\n\nRead the existing files and apply patches.",
