 code calls m_display.init(115200); without custom SPI.begin. That will use default SPI pins which are the same (23,18,5). So it's okay. The setMosi/setSck are not standard GxEPD2 methods; I think they don't exist. That might cause compilation error. We should revert those or replace with SPI.begin.\n\nBetter approach: In Display::begin(), before display.init(), call SPI.begin(EINK_SCLK, -1, EINK_MOSI, EINK_CS). This configures the VSPI bus with our custom pins (even though they match defaults). Remove the setMosi/setSck calls.\n\nAlso note: We've changed the sensor pin from 4 to 2 in src/main.cpp. Is GPIO2 safe? Yes, GPIO2 is ADC1 channel 2. It works.\n\nLet's update Display.cpp to fix the SPI initialization and remove non-existent methods.\n\nThen verify all changes.",
