many display-specific headers. But the error says the file is not found, which means either the library version does not include that header, or we need to install a different version (maybe the develop branch). Let's check the GxEPD2 documentation for WeAct 2.13\".\n\nFrom the browse of GxEPD2_BW.h, line 1 shows it's 823 lines. At the end of the file, there should be includes for display types. The snippet only showed the beginning. Let's open the file directly from GitHub to see the includes: https://github.com/ZinggJM/GxEPD2/blob/master/src/GxEPD2_BW.h\n\nWe can use the raw content to see the includes. Let's fetch the raw file.",
