      },
      {
        "type": "reasoning",
        "content": "The web search results don't provide a clear fix. The issue is that ESPAsyncWebServer 3.7.0 still has HTTP_GET/HTTP_ANY not declared. This usually happens because the library expects WebServer.h from the ESP32 core (which defines these constants) to be included, but the order matters, or the newer ESP32 Arduino core moved these definitions.\n\nLet me check what version of ESPAsyncWebServer actually works with ESP32-S3 Arduino core 3.x. The error `HTTP_GET was not declared in this scope` means the library uses HTTP_GET but the ESP32 core's WebServer.h or HTTPMethod.h is not included. In recent ESP32 Arduino core, HTTP_GET and friends are defined in `HTTPMethod.h` which is included by `WebServer.h`. The ESPAsyncWebServer should include `WebServer.h` or `HTTPMethod.h` itself, but version 3.6.0/3.7.0 may rely on the user including them first.\n\nLet me check what includes are in the WebServer.h of the library. Also check the library's own includes. Perhaps the fix is to include `<HTTPMethod.h>` before `<ESPAsyncWebServer.h>` in our WebServer.h.\n\nLet me also consider using mathieucarbou's fork or dvarrel's fork which may be compatible.\n\nActually, looking at the error more carefully: the error is in `ESPAsyncWebServer.h` itself, line 272, using `HTTP_GET`. This means the library is compiled without the ESP32 HTTP method definitions. The older version 3.6.0 maybe worked with earlier ESP32 core but not with 3.0.x (which changed where HTTPMethod.h is).\n\nLet me search more specifically.",
        "timestamp": 1781447858402
      },
      {
        "type": "reasoning",
        "content": "The user wants me to fix the compilation error where HTTP_GET and HTTP_ANY are not declared in HTTPMethod.h. This is a known issue with ESPAsyncWebServer on newer Arduino cores. The fix is to include `<HTTPMethod.h>` or to define HTTP_GET etc. manually, or to add `-DHTTP_GET=0x01` and `-DHTTP_ANY=0x06` build flags in platformio.ini. Alternatively, we can use a patched version of the library like `mathieucarbou/ESPAsyncWebServer @ 3.7.0` with its corresponding `AsyncTCP` version.\n\nLet me also check if `mathieucarbou/ESPAsyncWebServer` is published on PlatformIO registry. But the simplest fix is to add the defines to build_flags in platformio.ini.\n\nLet me recall that the error is in ESPAsyncWebServer.h line 272: `HTTP_GET` was not declared. This is because the library uses `HTTP_GET`, `HTTP_ANY` etc. which were previously defined in ESP8266WebServer.h or something similar but in the new Arduino core they are in `<HTTPMethod.h>` which not all libraries include. \n\nA known fix is to add:\n```cpp\n#include <HTTPMethod.h>\n```\nBut that might not exist. Better approach: add `-DHTTP_METHOD_H` or `-DHTTP_GET=0x01` flags.\n\nLet me search quickly for the actual fix.\n\nActually the answer from stackoverflow suggests:\n1. Include `<WebServer.h>` before ESPAsyncWebServer (but not ideal)\n2. Or define the constants manually.\n\nLet me try adding `build_flags = -DARDUINO_USB_CDC_ON_BOOT=1 -DHTTP_GET=0x01 -DHTTP_POST=0x02 -DHTTP_PUT=0x03 -DHTTP_HEAD=0x04 -DHTTP_DELETE=0x05 -DHTTP_ANY=0x06` in platformio.ini.\n\nThat should fix it.",
