        "type": "reasoning",
        "content": "We need to fix the build. The ESPAsyncWebServer library from me-no-dev is not found with version 3.7.0. Let me check the correct registry path. From the web search, the PlatformIO registry ID is ESP32Async/ESPAsyncWebServer. Also we can use the original me-no-dev/ESPAsyncWebServer but without version pinning to let PlatformIO resolve. However earlier we saw version 3.11.1 works but had conflict with AsyncTCP. The error was about HTTP_GET not declared in scope, which happened with 3.6.0 but not with 3.11.1? Actually 3.11.1 compiled our code but had other issues with RPAsyncTCP etc. So maybe we should use ESP32Async/ESPAsyncWebServer @ 3.11.1 and keep the build_flags for HTTP_METHOD? Actually the HTTP_GET error appeared with 3.6.0 but earlier we used 3.11.1 and it compiled our code but had other library conflicts (RPAsyncTCP, ESPAsyncTCP). The real problem was multiple AsyncTCP variants being pulled by different lib dependencies.\n\nLet me check the current platformio.ini and rewrite it to use:\n- ESP32Async/ESPAsyncWebServer (or ESP32Async/ESPAsyncWebServer @ 3.11.1)\n- ESP32Async/AsyncTCP (matching version needed by that)\n\nPlus add build_flags to define HTTP_METHOD_ macros if needed, but maybe they are already defined in the newer version. The error with old version was HTTP_GET not declared. The fix is either upgrade to a version that includes WebServer.h (which includes ESPAsyncWebServer.h → HTTP_METHOD.h) or add #include <HTTPMethod.h> before using ESPAsyncWebServer. But newer version likely includes it.\n\nLet me rewrite platformio.ini to use ESP32Async/ESPAsyncWebServer @ 3.11.1 and its matching AsyncTCP @ 3.x, and ensure no other AsyncTCP variants conflict. Also keep build_flags for USB CDC.\n\nThen clean and rebuild.",
