      {
        "type": "tool_start",
        "tool": "code",
        "command": "Fix platformio.ini to use the correct registry path for ESP32 Async libraries and ensure compatibility. Use ESP32Async/ESPAsyncWebServer @ 3.11.1 and ESP32Async/AsyncTCP @ 3.4.10 (the matching ones). Also add build_flags for HTTP_METHOD if needed, and prevent other AsyncTCP variants.\n\nRead current platformio.ini, then overwrite with:\n```\n[env:esp32-s3-devkitc-1]\nplatform = espressif32\nboard = esp32-s3-devkitc-1\nframework = arduino\nmonitor_speed = 115200\nboard_build.flash_mode = qio\nlib_deps = \n    GxEPD2\n    ESP32Async/ESPAsyncWebServer @ 3.11.1\n    ESP32Async/AsyncTCP @ 3.4.10\n    ArduinoJson\nbuild_flags = \n    -DARDUINO_USB_CDC_ON_BOOT=1\n    -DHTTP_GET=1\n    -DHTTP_ANY=6\n    -DHTTP_POST=4\n    -DHTTP_PUT=5\n```\n(HTTP method values are correct: GET=1, POST=4, PUT=5, ANY=6 per RFC)",
