rmIO adds `lib/` as a search path? It adds each library's own directory. So for Calibration, the include directories would include `lib/Calibration/` but not `lib/`. So relative from Calibration.h, `\"../Common/Types.h\"` works because `..` goes to `lib/`. Similarly for Display.h, `\"../Common/Types.h\"` works.\n\nBut also, Sensor.h: currently doesn't include Types.h, but it defines MAX_SENSORS = 4, while Types.h defines MAX_SENSORS = 5. We need to align. Sensor.h should include Types.h or use the same constant. Let's change Sensor.h to include `\"../Common/Types.h\"` (relative) and use `MAX_SENSORS` from Types.h. And remove its own `MAX_SENSORS` definition.\n\nWebServer.h includes `\"Types.h\"` and `\"SensorManager.h\"`. The `\"Types.h\"` needs to be `\"../Common/Types.h\"`. The `\"SensorManager.h\"` should be `\"../Sensor/Sensor.h\"` (since Sensor.h defines SensorManager class). Or we could rename Sensor.h to SensorManager.h? That would cause include path issues. Better keep as Sensor.h and include with relative path.\n\nLet's do a pass over all includes to fix them.",
