        "content": "## Active Plan\n► [1] Read all current source files (Sensor, Calibration, Preferences, WebServer, Display, main.cpp) to understand interfaces (in_progress)\n⊘ [2] Refactor Preferences to store per-sensor calibration (dry/wet values), field names, and ADC pins as a JSON array. Add methods: loadSensorConfig(uint8_t index), saveSensorConfig(uint8_t index, ...), loadAllConfigs(...) (blocked)\n   deps: 1\n⊘ [3] Refactor Calibration to accept sensor index in constructor and provide getCalibratedValue(index, raw). Move calibration storage to Preferences. Remove old singleton pattern. (blocked)\n   deps: 2\n⊘ [4] Refactor Sensor class to manage an array of sensor instances. Constructor takes list of pins, initializes ADC. Provide getValues() returning array of raw readings, and getCount(). Reading is done sequentially for each pin. (blocked)\n   deps: 3\n⊘ [5] Refactor WebServer to expose new REST API: GET /api/sensors (list with names, raw, calibrated, dry, wet), POST /api/calibrate/{index} (body: {dry: raw} or {wet: raw}), POST /api/config/{index} (body: {name: string}). Use existing async patterns. (blocked)\n   deps: 4\n⊘ [6] Update Display to show all sensors on e-paper (list field name and percentage). Use multiple lines on the 250×122 screen. Adjust layout for up to 5 values. (blocked)\n   deps: 5\n⊘ [7] Update main.cpp to wire everything together: define array of ADC pins (GPIO1..6 etc.), initialize Sensor with array, pass to Calibration, WebServer, Display. Call periodic reading and display update. (blocked)\n   deps: 6\n⊘ [8] Verify compilation is clean, fix any issues (blocked)\n   deps: 7",
