        "content": "We have read the files. The current Calibration class no longer has `getPin`, `getDryValue`, `getWetValue` methods; it uses `loadAllConfigs` to populate external array. SensorManager currently uses `cal->getPin(i)` etc., but Calibration doesn't have those. We need to refactor SensorManager to work with the new Calibration. Options:\n\n- Add getPin/getDryValue/getWetValue to Calibration that query the internal m_configs array.\n- Or have SensorManager not use Calibration directly; instead Calibration provides configs array and SensorManager reads from it.\n\nSimplest: add those accessor methods to Calibration that return from m_configs. That would minimize changes to SensorManager.\n\nAlso SensorManager currently has begin that takes Calibration pointer and reads config from it. This is fine if Calibration has those methods.\n\nSo plan:\n\n1. Add following methods to Calibration:\n   - `uint8_t getPin(uint8_t index) const;`\n   - `int getDryValue(uint8_t index) const;`\n   - `int getWetValue(uint8_t index) const;`\n   - `const char* getName(uint8_t index) const;`\n   They return from m_configs[index] (after ensuring index < m_count).\n\n2. Modify Calibration::begin to accept an array of default pins and count, and call loadAllConfigs to populate m_configs.\n\n3. SensorManager::begin already works, but we need to make sure Calibration has those getters.\n\n4. Also SensorManager currently has `setCalibration` that sets dry/wet in its internal state; but actual saving is done via Calibration. In `setCalibration`, after updating sensor array, should also call `cal->setDryRaw(index, dry); cal->setWetRaw(index, wet);` so that it persists. But that would cause immediate save. That's fine for calibration flow.\n\n5. In WebServer and main.cpp, they currently use `sensor.setCalibration(...)` and `calibration.setDryValue(...)` etc. We need to adjust to new API.\n\nLet's proceed stepwise.\n\nFirst, update Calibration to add getters and modify begin signature to accept defaults.\n\nThen adjust SensorManager to call cal->setDryRaw/setWetRaw in setCalibration. Also remove setCalibration? Actually it's needed for the sensor to know thresholds without reading calibration every loop. But we can keep local cache and update both.\n\nThen update main.cpp.\n\nThen WebServer.\n\nLet's do it.",
