The Sensor.cpp uses `cal->getPin(i)`, `cal->getDryValue(i)`, `cal->getWetValue(i)`. But the new Calibration.h doesn't have those methods. Wait, earlier in the code agent diff for Calibration.h, it showed \"Updated Calibration.h with getters and changed begin() signature\". So the getters were added? Let's check the file content. The last read of Calibration.h (before the update) didn't have getters. The code agent said \"Updated Calibration.h with getters\". We need to verify.\n\nFor now, we know we need to update Sensor to use the new Calibration interface, but we must ensure Calibration has the needed methods. Let's read the current Calibration.h to confirm.\n\nAlso, we need to update WebServer.cpp to use new API (readRaw, readPercent, readVoltage vs getRaw, getPercent...). SensorManager uses getRaw/getPercent, WebServer uses sensorManager->readRaw(i) etc. In WebServer.cpp lines 56-58 it uses `sensorManager->readRaw(i)`, `sensorManager->readPercent(i)`, `sensorManager->readVoltage(i)`. But SensorManager has `getRaw`, `getPercent`, `getVoltage`. So either SensorManager needs to have `readRaw` as alias, or WebServer needs to use `getRaw`. In the current Sensor.h, methods are `getRaw`, `getPercent`, `getVoltage`. WebServer.cpp uses `readRaw` which doesn't exist. Also calibration methods used `setDryValue`, `getName`, etc. So there's a mismatch.\n\nWe need to fix all these inconsistencies. So the next step should be to update SensorManager to add readRaw/readPercent/readVoltage methods (or alias) and ensure Calibration has the necessary getters (getName, getDryValue, getWetValue). And then update WebServer to match.\n\nBut the plan says step 4 is refactor Sensor, step 5 is refactor WebServer. Perhaps we can combine them in one code call after ensuring Calibration is correct.\n\nLet's read Calibration.h again first.",
