        "content": "### User Goal\nRefactor the ESP32-S3 plant watering system to support up to 5 capacitive soil moisture sensors with per-sensor calibration, field naming, and web interface management, with persistence across reboots.\n\n### What Was Done\n- Read all project source files (Sensor, Calibration, WebServer, Display, main.cpp, platformio.ini) to understand current interfaces.\n- Created `lib/Common/Types.h` with `MAX_SENSORS=5` and `SensorConfig` struct (name[32], pin, dryRaw, wetRaw).\n- Refactored `Calibration` class: stores all sensor configs as a single JSON object in NVS (namespace \"calib\", key \"config\"). Added getters and setters for per-sensor values.\n- Updated `SensorManager` class: uses array of `SensorInfo` (pin, dry, wet, name). `setCalibration` persists via `Calibration`.\n- Updated `Display` class to iterate over active sensors and show name + humidity percentage.\n- Compiled successfully after each refactor; no errors.\n\n### Current State\nThe codebase has been refactored to support multiple sensors. `Calibration` and `SensorManager` are complete. The last action was reading `WebServer.h` and `WebServer.cpp` to plan updates for multi-sensor API.\n\n### Pending / Next Steps\n- Update `WebServer` implementation: add per-sensor calibration endpoints (`/calibrate/{index}`), configuration endpoint for field names, and status endpoint returning all sensor readings.\n- Update `main.cpp` if constructor signatures changed.\n- Update HTML frontend (`index.h`) to display and manage multiple sensors.\n- Test on hardware.\n\n### Key Context\n- Board: ESP32-S3-DevKitC-1\n- Framework: Arduino (PlatformIO)\n- Display pins: BUSY=4, RES=16, D/C=17, CS=5, SCL=18, MOSI=21\n- Sensor ADC pins: use ADC1 (GPIO1-10) to avoid WiFi interference\n- Libraries: ESPAsyncWebServer, AsyncTCP, GxEPD2, Adafruit GFX, ArduinoJson 7.4.3, Preferences\n- Calibration stored in NVS namespace \"calib\", key \"config\"\n- Names limited to 32 characters\n- WiFi credentials stored in Preferences (namespace \"wifi\")",
