        "type": "reasoning",
        "content": "The include path \"Common/Types.h\" needs to be relative to the src folder. In PlatformIO, when you #include a file from lib/, you need the correct relative path. The file is at lib/Common/Types.h. From src/main.cpp, the include should be \"../lib/Common/Types.h\" or better, add the path to platformio.ini include paths. The simplest fix: change the include in main.cpp to \"../../lib/Common/Types.h\"? No, PlatformIO automatically adds lib/ folders to include path for library includes, but only if the library is declared as a library in platformio.ini. But Common is not a library with a library.json, it's just a folder.\n\nBest approach: add an include path in platformio.ini build_flags: `-Ilib/Common`. Then we can just `#include \"Types.h\"`. But that would break Calibration.h's include.\n\nBetter: the existing includes like `#include \"../Common/Types.h\"` in Calibration.h work because Calibration.cpp is in lib/Calibration/ and the relative path goes up one directory then into Common. For src/main.cpp, the relative path would be `../lib/Common/Types.h`. But that's ugly.\n\nHowever, looking at the existing code: Calibration.h already uses `#include \"../Common/Types.h\"`, and in main.cpp we have `#include \"Common/Types.h\"` which is wrong. We should either change to `#include \"../lib/Common/Types.h\"` or add a build flag `-Ilib`.\n\nThe cleanest is to add `build_flags = -Ilib` to platformio.ini so that `#include \"Common/Types.h\"` works from all files. But we must ensure no name conflicts.\n\nLet's instead change the include in main.cpp to the relative path that works: `#include \"../lib/Common/Types.h\"`.\n\nAlternatively, add platformio.ini build_flags `-Ilib` and change all includes to `#include \"Common/Types.h\"`.\n\nI'll go with adding include path because it's cleaner. Will update platformio.ini and also fix main.cpp if needed.",
