        "type": "reasoning",
        "content": "We need to rewrite the routes to use query parameters instead of path parameters. The routes currently use `:index` syntax which causes compilation error because pathArg() requires ASYNCWEBSERVER_REGEX and regex handlers. We can either define ASYNCWEBSERVER_REGEX as a build flag, or switch to query parameters.\n\nI think the simplest and most reliable fix is to add `-DASYNCWEBSERVER_REGEX` to build_flags in platformio.ini. That way the path parameter syntax with `:index` and `pathArg()` will work as intended.\n\nLet's do that. Also fix the deprecation warnings in Calibration.cpp and WebServer.cpp regarding DynamicJsonDocument and createNestedObject/createNestedArray. We'll replace with modern syntax:\n- `DynamicJsonDocument` -> `JsonDocument` (already done in WebServer.cpp)\n- `createNestedArray(\"sensors\")` -> `doc[\"sensors\"].to<JsonArray>()`\n- `sensors.createNestedObject()` -> `JsonObject sensor = sensors.add<JsonObject>()`\n- similarly in Calibration.cpp for saveAllConfigs\n\nBut the immediate blocker is the ASYNCWEBSERVER_REGEX error. Let's add that build flag. Then recompile. If that works, we can fix deprecation warnings later.\n\nLet me plan:\n1. Update platformio.ini to add -DASYNCWEBSERVER_REGEX\n2. Recompile",
