        "type": "reasoning",
        "content": "The user wants me to fix the compilation error. The error is: `pathArg() requires -D ASYNCWEBSERVER_REGEX and only works on regex handlers`. I have two options:\n\n1. Add `-DASYNCWEBSERVER_REGEX` to build_flags and use regex routes\n2. Change routes to use query parameters (`?index=0`) and `request->arg(\"index\")` instead of `request->pathArg(0)`\n\nOption 2 is simpler and avoids regex overhead. Let me rewrite the four routes to use query parameters.\n\nThe routes to change:\n- `/api/calibrate/dry/:index` → `/api/calibrate/dry` with query param `index`\n- `/api/calibrate/wet/:index` → `/api/calibrate/wet` with query param `index`\n- `/api/calibrate/reset/:index` → `/api/calibrate/reset` with query param `index`\n- `/api/config/sensor/:index` → `/api/config/sensor` with query param `index`\n\nNeed to replace `request->pathArg(0)` with `request->arg(\"index\")`.\n\nI'll produce a single code action to replace the WebServer.cpp content with these fixes.",
