        "content": "The user has a WeActStudio 2.13\" e-ink display that is actually tri-color (black, white, red), but they want only black and white display. Currently the code uses `GxEPD2_BW<GxEPD2_213_BN, ...>` which is for black/white. The issue is likely that the display expects a different driver for tri-color, or the init sends color data causing unwanted red. They also want to remove the \"Moisture Monitor\" title, update only when values change (using fast partial update), and add WiFi settings page to the web interface.\n\nLet me first search for the correct display type. WeActStudio 2.13\" tri-color might be GxEPD2_213c or GxEPD2_213_Z19c etc. But they want to force black/white only, ignoring red. We can still use GxEPD2_BW but need to ensure the display is initialized correctly not to show red. Actually tri-color e-papers have a different internal structure; there's a separate red/black variant. The WeAct 2.13\" tri-color I think uses SSD1680, but the driver in GxEPD2_BW might still work, but the red color might appear as black or not clear properly. Actually looking at GxEPD2, there are specific classes for tri-color: GxEPD2_3C, GxEPD2_4C etc. The GxEPD2_213_BN is black/white. For tri-color, there is GxEPD2_213c (or GxEPD2_213_B72, B73, B74? No, those are other). Let me search memory or recall.\n\nFrom memory: WeAct 2.13\" tri-color is likely GxEPD2_213c or GxEPD2_213_B73? Actually the model number often is GDEY0213B74 (black, white, red). The GxEPD2 library has GxEPD2_213_B74 for that. But to force black/white only, we can use the tri-color class but only draw in black/white (don't use red). However, the user says it's showing red when it shouldn't. This suggests the display is being treated as black/white but actually has red, and maybe the initial screen or a double refresh causes red to appear. Solution: use the correct tri-color driver, but only draw black/white (no red). That will ensure proper behavior. Or we can keep black/white driver but after updating, the display might have residual red. Tri-color e-papers often have a different SPI command set. The best is to switch to GxEPD2_BW? That's for true BW displays. For tri-color, we need GxEPD2_3C. However, if the display is forced to only black/white, it might still work but with potential artifacts. The user explicitly wants black/white only. So we should use the tri-color driver but never use red color.\n\nActually reading the user: \"у него три цвета - черный, белый и красный. надо чтобы был только черно - белый.\" So the display is tri-color, but they want only black/white rendering. The current code uses GxEPD2_BW with GxEPD2_213_BN which is a black/white type. That type might not be correct for a tri-color display, causing garbled colors. I need to find the correct display class for WeAct Studio 2.13\" tri-color. Let me quickly search the GxEPD2 source or recall.\n\nCommon WeAct tri-color e-paper modules: often labelled as \"2.13 inch e-Paper Display Module\" with SSD1680 controller. For tri-color, the GxEPD2 class is GxEPD2_213_B74 (or B72, B73). Actually looking at GxEPD2_BW.h includes epd/GxEPD2_213_B74.h. And there is also gdey/GxEPD2_213_GDEY0213B74.h. I think the appropriate for tri-color is to include GxEPD2_3C.h instead of GxEPD2_BW.h, and use GxEPD2_213c? Let me check online quickly.\n\nBut I can also reason: the current code uses GxEPD2_213_BN which is black/white. The display is showing red, which means it's actually a tri-color and the GxEPD2_BW driver may be sending commands that are misinterpreted. To fix, we should use the correct tri-color class from GxEPD2 (GxEPD2_3C or GxEPD2_213c). And then only draw in black/white (no red). That will force black/white only. The title \"Moisture Monitor\" can be removed. Also implement partial update.\n\nFor partial update: GxEPD2 supports setPartialWindow and has hasFastPartialUpdate. We can implement a comparison of the last drawn content to detect changes. Since e-ink only needs update when values change.\n\nFor WiFi settings: the index.html currently doesn't have a settings page for WiFi. We need to add a modal or page that lists current WiFi info and has a form to change SSID/password. Also the captive portal is reached via /wifi page. But when connected to home WiFi, there's no way to reconfigure WiFi. We can add a settings button in the web UI that shows WiFi info and a reconfigure form.\n\nLet me plan the subtasks.\n\nI'll create a plan.",
