        "content": "We need to fix the three issues:\n\n1. Tri-color display is showing red for black areas because GxEPD2_213_BN (Black/White) constructor is being passed to a GxEPD2_BW template, but if the display is actually a tri-color variant (GxEPD2_213_B72, GxEPD2_213_B73, GxEPD2_213_B74, GxEPD2_213_M21, etc.) then the constructor might be wrong. But user says \"три цвета - черный, белый и красный\" so it's a tri-color display. However they want only black and white. The issue is that the library might be sending red pixels where black should be because the HC/CS low? Actually, tri-color e-ink displays have two types: B/W/R (black/white/red) and B/W/Y. The WeActStudio 2.13\" inch has several variants: BWR (black-white-red) or BW (black-white). The user says it's tri-color but they want only black-white. The GxEPD2 library has different display classes for tri-color: GxEPD2_3C, GxEPD2_213_Z19c, GxEPD2_213c etc. But currently they're using GxEPD2_BW with GxEPD2_213_BN which is black/white only. If the actual display is tri-color, the initialization might be wrong, causing artifacts.\n\nBut the user says \"сейчас он почему то красным отображает на экране\" meaning it shows red instead of black? Possibly the tri-color display driver is being incorrectly used as BW, causing red to appear where black should be. Or the display is BW but the library is outputting red due to a configuration issue. The user wants only black and white. So we need to ensure the driver is set for BW mode only.\n\nLooking at the display type: WeActStudio 2.13\" comes in several models:\n- GxEPD2_213_BN (black/white)\n- GxEPD2_213_B72 (black/white/red)\n- GxEPD2_213_B73 (black/white/red)\n- GxEPD2_213_B74 (black/white/red)\n- GxEPD2_213_M21 (black/white/red)\n- GxEPD2_213_BN is BW only.\n\nThe user said \"три цвета\", so it's a tri-color display, but they want only black-white. We need to change the display type to the tri-color version but only use black and white, or if we can't, then we need to ensure GxEPD2_BW is used with the correct display type that matches tri-color but only outputs black/white.\n\nActually, GxEPD2_BW can be used with tri-color displays, but then only black and white are used. The constructor should be GxEPD2_213_B72 (for example) instead of GxEPD2_213_BN. But they're using GxEPD2_213_BN which is specifically for BW-only displays. If the actual display is tri-color, using BN might cause timing issues or incorrect waveform leading to red artifacts.\n\nSo we should change to use a tri-color display type like GxEPD2_213_B72 or GxEPD2_213_B73, but still with GxEPD2_BW? Actually GxEPD2_BW is for BW only, there's GxEPD2_3C for tri-color. But if we use GxEPD2_3C with a tri-color display, it will output red/black/white. To output only black/white, we should either:\n- Force black color only (don't use red)\n- Use GxEPD2_BW with a tri-color display type (some drivers support this, but need to select the right type)\n\nBetter approach: Switch to GxEPD2_3C with a tri-color display type (e.g., GxEPD2_213_B72 or GxEPD2_213_B73 or GxEPD2_213_B74), but ensure we only set text color to GxEPD_BLACK and fill with GxEPD_WHITE, never GxEPD_RED. That way it will only use black and white. But the full refresh might still flash red due to the waveform? The waveform for tri-color might still flash red, but the final display will be black and white only.\n\nAlternatively, check if there's a way to put the display in BW-only mode via a command.\n\nSince WeActStudio 2.13\" tri-color is likely GxEPD2_213_B73 or GxEPD2_213_B74. Let's assume GxEPD2_213_B73 (common with WeActStudio). We'll use GxEPD2_3C<GxEPD2_213_B73, 250> instead of GxEPD2_BW<GxEPD2_213_BN, 250>. But we want to display only black/white. However, the tri-color display waveform includes a red phase, but if no red pixels are drawn, it should just flash red then stabilize? Actually in partial update mode, the red might not appear. But full refresh might show red where black would be if not properly initialized.\n\nBetter: Use GxEPD2_BW with tri-color display type, because the library documentation says GxEPD2_BW can be used with tri-color displays for black/white only operation: \"use GxEPD2_BW for black/white only, even for tri-color displays\". The constructor just needs the right display type. So we should change GxEPD2_213_BN to GxEPD2_213_B73 (or whichever matches the user's display). \n\nThe user didn't specify exact model, but typical WeActStudio 2.13\" tri-color is GxEPD2_213_B73 or GxEPD2_213_B74. We'll use GxEPD2_213_B73 as it's most common with that board.\n\nBut we also need to change #include from GxEPD2_BW.h to GxEPD2_213_B73.h? Actually GxEPD2_213_B73.h is included automatically by GxEPD2_BW.h via __has_include. The template parameter remains GxEPD2_BW. So we just change the display type.\n\nSo in Display.h:\n- Change #include <GxEPD2_BW.h> (keep)\n- Change template parameter from GxEPD2_213_BN to GxEPD2_213_B73 (or B74)\n- Change constructor call accordingly\n\nBut the user wants to remove the \"Moisture Monitor\" title and only update display when changes occur, using fast partial update.\n\nLet's also address the update logic: Currently showStatus does a full refresh every time. We should change to partial update only when values have changed. We'll add a method to check if any value changed and only then update. Use setPartialWindow and display(true) for partial refresh.\n\nFor fast refresh: GxEPD2 supports partial update if supported by the display. For tri-color displays, partial update might not be supported for the red layer, but if we use BW mode, we can use partial update.\n\nWe'll also remove \"Moisture Monitor\" title and shift lines up.\n\nFinally, the web interface: The user wants settings page for WiFi and sensor names. Currently the web UI is in index.h. We need to add a settings page (maybe a modal or separate tab) with fields: WiFi SSID, WiFi password, and for each sensor a name field. We'll also need POST endpoints for WiFi config and sensor name (already exist). The settings page should be accessible from a button.\n\nNow, let's construct a plan with tasks.\n\nWe need to:\n- Update Display.h to use tri-color display type but in BW mode\n- Update Display.cpp to remove title, shift lines up, add partial update logic only on change\n- Update index.h to add settings page (settings button, modal/panel for WiFi and sensor names)\n- Potentially update WebServer.cpp if we need new endpoints (the existing /wifi and /api/config/sensor?index= may suffice)\n\nBut the user said \"в веб интерфейсе нет настроек и не ввести wifi\". Currently the web UI doesn't have WiFi settings; only the captive portal page at /wifi has it. The main UI is a separate page that doesn't include WiFi settings. So we should integrate WiFi settings into the main UI as a settings page/module.\n\nPlan tasks:\n1. Read index.h to understand current UI\n2. Update Display.h/cpp for correct display type, partial update, remove title\n3. Update index.h: add settings button, modal for WiFi and sensor name configuration\n4. Build and test",
