        "type": "reasoning",
        "content": "We need to proceed with the plan. Step 1 (read current files) is done. Now step 2: Update Display.cpp to remove title, track last values for partial update, and avoid full refresh unless needed.\n\nBut we also need to update Display.h to use a tri-color display type correctly. The user's display has three colors (black, white, red). GxEPD2 supports tri-color with GxEPD2_3C class. For WeActStudio 2.13\" tri-color, the class is GxEPD2_213_B73 (black, white, red). But the user wants only black/white, so we can use GxEPD2_3C and only draw in black/white (ignore red). However, the GxEPD2_3C constructor takes the same pin args.\n\nBut we already changed Display.h to use GxEPD2_3C<GxEPD2_213_B73, ...>. Good.\n\nNow we need to also change Display.cpp to remove the title \"Moisture Monitor\", adjust yStart accordingly, and implement partial update. Also we need to add a method to track whether the content has changed, and only call display() then. But GxEPD2's partial update is tricky; we can use `m_display.setPartialWindow()` and `m_display.nextPage()` loop for the voltage area only, but the simplest is to track content hash and only do full update when changed, and use partial update for small changes? However, for frequent updates, e-ink displays can burn out. Better to only update at fixed interval (10 seconds) as before, but we can skip if no change.\n\nLet's implement a dirty flag: we store last displayed values, and only update if current differs from last.\n\nAdjust Display.cpp:\n- Add struct PreviousState with arrays of int percentages and int raw.\n- In setup, fill with -1 initially.\n- In showStatus, when sensorCount, percentages, rawValues haven't changed compared to stored previous, skip the whole display call.\n- If they have, update, call m_display.display(false) always (full refresh). Partial update is risky.\n\nBut the user asked \"обновлять экран надо только тогда когда есть изменение и делать это через быстрый рефреш\". Fast refresh might be partial update. We can try `m_display.display(true)` for partial update after first full refresh? GxEPD2 supports `init(115200, true, 50, false)` where second parameter is initial full refresh. Then subsequent updates can use `display(true)` for partial. But we need to ensure we don't call full refresh every time.\n\nSimpler: on first call, full refresh; on subsequent calls, use `display(true)` for partial if the display supports fast partial update. GxEPD2_213_B73 supports partial update? According to GxEPD2, many displays support it. We can try: after `m_display.init(115200, true)` (full initial), then later call `m_display.display(true)` for partial. But for simplicity, we can just use full refresh every time until we encounter issues.\n\nGiven the user's request, I'll implement a \"dirty\" check: compare current values to previous, if same skip; if different, call full refresh. That's safe.\n\nAlso shift yStart from 45 to 10 to remove title margin.\n\nNow we also need to update index.h: calibration URLs use path parameters like `/api/calibrate/dry/${index}` but server expects query parameter `?index=N`. Need to fix fetch URLs in index.h.\n\nAlso add a settings button to configure WiFi: maybe a gear icon that shows a modal with current SSID (from /api/wifi) and ability to change (POST /api/config/wifi). But the user just said \"в веб интерфейсе нет настроек и не ввести wifi\". So we need to add a settings page/modal for WiFi configuration.\n\nLet's do all in one code task: rewrite Display.cpp and update index.h with fixed URLs and settings modal. Also add a /api/wifi endpoint to get current SSID.\n\nLet's plan:\n\n1. Update Display.cpp: remove title, adjust yStart, add previous state tracking, skip if unchanged.\n2. Update index.h: fix calibration URL to use query parameter ?index=, add settings button, add modal/section for WiFi config (SSID/password input), fetch current SSID from /api/wifi on page load, POST to /api/config/wifi.\n3. Update WebServer.cpp: add GET /api/wifi (returns {ssid: ...}), POST /api/config/wifi (saves ssid/pass and restarts).\n4. Update WebServer.h if needed.\n\nThat's substantial. I'll combine 2,3 into one multi-file code task.\n\nLet's proceed.",
