        "type": "reasoning",
        "content": "The user wants to fix the tri-color display to only show black/white, remove the \"Moisture Monitor\" title, add partial update on change, and integrate WiFi/settings into web UI. They also mentioned that the display shows red when it should be black/white only.\n\nFrom the search results, I found that:\n- GxEPD2_213_BN is the correct class for the black/white 2.13\" display\n- GxEPD2_213_Z98c is for tri-color (black/white/red) displays\n\nThe user's display is tri-color (black, white, red) but they want only black and white output. The current code uses GxEPD2_BW<GxEPD2_213_BN> which is for BW-only displays. But the actual hardware might be a tri-color version that needs the 3C class but used in BW mode.\n\nActually, looking at the error: \"GxEPD2_213_B73 was not declared\" - that's the tri-color version of 2.13\". The BW version is GxEPD2_213_BN. The user says the display shows black/white/red but they want only black/white. So the hardware is tri-color (B73 or Z98c) but they want to output only black/white.\n\nThe simplest approach: stay with GxEPD2_BW<GxEPD2_213_BN> which should work for any 2.13\" display - it just doesn't use the red channel. The user said \"сейчас он почему то красным отображает на экране\" - it's displaying red - meaning somewhere in the code we're using the red channel. But with GxEPD2_BN (black/white only), there is no red channel, so it shouldn't be using red. Unless the hardware reports itself as a tri-color display but we're using only black/white... \n\nActually, the real issue might be that the display module is tri-color and requires the 3C constructor. When using GxEPD2_BW, it might not initialize correctly, causing random colors or leftover red from a previous full refresh. Or maybe the constructor with GxEPD2_213_BN is incorrect for this specific module.\n\nLooking at the user's hardware: \"weactstudio e-ink display 2.13\\\" and later said \"три цвета - черный, белый и красный\" - so it's tri-color. The correct display class for WeAct 2.13\" tri-color is GxEPD2_213_Z98c (SSD1680 controller with red). So we should use GxEPD2_3C<GxEPD2_213_Z98c> but only draw in black and white.\n\nBut the user's goal is \"надо чтобы был только черно - белый\" - they want black/white only, not using red. So we should use the tri-color class but never draw in red (only use GxEPD_BLACK and GxEPD_WHITE).\n\nHowever, the earlier error showed that GxEPD2_213_B73 was not found. The correct tri-color class is GxEPD2_213_Z98c. So we need to:\n1. Use GxEPD2_3C<GxEPD2_213_Z98c> instead of GxEPD2_BW<GxEPD2_213_BN>\n2. Include GxEPD2_3C.h instead of GxEPD2_BW.h\n3. Update the constructor in Display.cpp to use GxEPD2_213_Z98c\n\nBut wait, the user originally said \"как подключить\" and I used GxEPD2_BW<GxEPD2_213_BN>. That might be wrong for this display. The correct driver for WeActStudio 2.13\" tri-color is GxEPD2_213_Z98c (black/white/red) or GxEPD2_213_BN (black/white only). \n\nLooking at WeActStudio documentation, the 2.13\" module with three colors uses SSD1680 controller and the GxEPD2 class is GxEPD2_213_Z98c or GxEPD2_213c (for color). But the user complained about red showing, which means we're probably drawing with red accidentally.\n\nActually, in the current code, we call `m_display.setTextColor(GxEPD_BLACK)` and `m_display.fillScreen(GxEPD_WHITE)`. These should not produce red. So why is red appearing? Possibly because the display is using a tri-color driver but we're using the BW class, causing initialization issues. Or maybe it's a hardware defect (previous red content remains).\n\nLet me think about what the user actually needs:\n1. Fix the display to only show black/white (fix the red issue)\n2. Remove the \"Moisture Monitor\" title\n3. Use partial update only when values change\n4. Add WiFi settings to the web UI\n\nFrom the compilation output, the files now have:\n- Display.h with GxEPD2_BW<GxEPD2_213_BN> (black/white)\n- Display.cpp with partial update and dirty check\n\nThe compilation error was about GxEPD2_213_B73 not being declared, but I've reverted to GxEPD2_213_BN. Let me fix the actual issue properly: the user's display is tri-color (GxEPD2_213_Z98c), and I need to use GxEPD2_3C class but only draw in black/white.\n\nBut the compilation succeeded with GxEPD2_213_BN earlier. The issue now is just red content. Maybe the display driver is actually GxEPD2_213_BN (black/white) and the red is coming from a previous state that wasn't cleared properly.\n\nLet me check the display driver more carefully. WeActStudio 2.13\" e-ink module comes in two variants:\n- Black/white only: uses GxEPD2_213_BN (or GxEPD2_213)\n- Black/white/red: uses GxEPD2_213_Z98c or GxEPD2_213c\n\nThe user said \"три цвета\" - so it's the tri-color version. For that, we need GxEPD2_3C, not GxEPD2_BW. But the user only wants black/white output.\n\nSo the correct fix is:\n1. Use GxEPD2_3C<GxEPD2_213_Z98c, GxEPD2_213_Z98c::HEIGHT> m_display;\n2. Include GxEPD2_3C.h\n3. In all drawing, only use GxEPD_BLACK, GxEPD_WHITE, never GxEPD_RED\n\nLet me check if GxEPD2_213_Z98c exists in the library. From the browse result, I saw that GxEPD2_BW.h includes `#include \"epd/GxEPD2_213_BN.h\"` but there's also `#include \"epd3c/GxEPD2_213_Z98c.h\"` in the 3C variant.\n\nActually, looking at the GxEPD2_BW.h file I read earlier, it only includes BW types. The tri-color types are in GxEPD2_3C.h via epd3c includes. So to use the tri-color hardware, we must use GxEPD2_3C.\n\nLet me check if GxEPD2_3C.h is available by including it and using GxEPD2_3C with the tri-color class.\n\nPlan: \n1. Read the current state of Display.h and Display.cpp\n2. Fix Display.h to use GxEPD2_3C with GxEPD2_213_Z98c (or the appropriate tri-color class)\n3. Fix Display.cpp constructor\n4. Update web UI to add settings\n5. Build\n\nActually, I need to be more careful. Let me read the library's GxEPD2_3C.h to see what includes it has and what classes are available.",
