        "type": "reasoning",
        "content": "The user wants me to fix the tri-color display issue and compile. Let me update Display.cpp to use the correct constructor for GxEPD2_213_Z98c and also fix the text color to only use black/white.\n\nLooking at the errors, the issue is that GxEPD2_3C doesn't have those methods - it has firstPage/nextPage for multi-page rendering. Wait, actually the GxEPD2_3C class might have different API. Let me check the library.\n\nActually, looking at the GxEPD2 library, the 3-color displays do support fillScreen, setCursor, print etc. The issue might be that GxEPD2_213_Z98c is not being included. Let me check if GxEPD2_3C.h includes the necessary epd files.\n\nLooking at the browse result earlier, GxEPD2_BW.h includes all the epd files via __has_include. But for GxEPD2_3C, it might not include the tri-color variants. Let me check the library structure.\n\nActually, looking at the error from the build: `'GxEPD2_213_B73' was not declared in this scope`. The compiler found `GxEPD2_213_Z98c` as an alternative. So maybe the correct class for the WeAct 2.13\" tri-color display is `GxEPD2_213_Z98c`. But then all the methods fail because `m_display` becomes type int? That's weird - it means the template instantiation failed completely.\n\nWait, looking at the errors again: `m_display` is of non-class type 'int'. This means the template resulted in an int due to the error. So the issue is that `GxEPD2_213_Z98c` is also not known to the compiler.\n\nI need to include the correct header. For GxEPD2_3C, I need to include the epd3c subdirectory header. Let me check what GxEPD2_3C.h includes.\n\nActually, looking at the GxEPD2 library structure, GxEPD2_3C.h should have similar __has_include guards. Let me verify by building without the tri-color class first - just use BW on this panel.\n\nWait, the user said \"сейчас он почему то красным отображает на экране, у него три цвета - черный, белый и красный\". So the display is tri-color but showing red. The original code used GxEPD2_BW with GxEPD2_213_BN. That might be rendering red as black? Actually, the display is a tri-color panel, so using GxEPD2_213_BN (black/white) might be treating the display incorrectly and the red state might be showing unwanted red.\n\nThe correct approach: use the tri-color driver class but only use black and white colors. The tri-color classes are in GxEPD2_3C.h and use display classes like GxEPD2_213_Z98c.\n\nLet me check if GxEPD2_3C.h is available in the installed library (1.6.9). The user's build showed __has_include for epd3c files. So `GxEPD2_213_Z98c` should be available.\n\nThe key is to include the proper epd3c header. GxEPD2_3C.h includes epd3c files conditionally. But I also need to ensure that the API (fillScreen, print, etc.) works the same. It should, as GxEPD2_3C inherits from Adafruit_GFX.\n\nActually, looking at the build error more carefully:\n```\nlib/Display/Display.h:38:13: error: 'GxEPD2_213_B73' was not declared in this scope\n   GxEPD2_3C<GxEPD2_213_B73, GxEPD2_213_B73::HEIGHT> m_display;\n```\nAnd it suggested `GxEPD2_213_Z98c`. So my first attempt used B73 which doesn't exist. The suggestion Z98c does exist. Let me try Z98c.\n\nBut the errors about all methods being int suggest the template still failed. Let me check if GxEPD2_3C.h is properly included and if Z98c is within it.\n\nLet me just use the simplest fix: since the user wants black/white only and the display is tri-color, use GxEPD2_BW with GxEPD2_213_BN but ensure we only use GxEPD_BLACK and GxEPD_WHITE colors. The red issue might be because the BN driver is for black/white only, but on a tri-color panel it might still work with only BW colors. If there's red appearing, it might be a hardware issue or the BN driver doesn't fully support the tri-color panel.\n\nAlternative: use GxEPD2_3C with GxEPD2_213_Z98c and explicitly only use GxEPD_BLACK and GxEPD_WHITE.\n\nLet me try the second approach. I need to also update Display.cpp constructor to use Z98c.\n\nBut first, I need to verify that GxEPD2_3C.h is present. The user's build did not show any error about missing GxEPD2_3C.h, only about the template argument. So GxEPD2_3C.h exists.\n\nI'll write a new version of Display.h that uses Z98c for tri-color, and update Display.cpp to use Z98c constructor.\n\nAlso, I need to ensure that the display doesn't show red. In a tri-color display, using only `setTextColor(GxEPD_BLACK)` and `fillScreen(GxEPD_WHITE)` should avoid red.\n\nLet me check if GxEPD2_3C has setTextColor with just black. Yes, the color constants are shared: GxEPD_BLACK, GxEPD_WHITE, GxEPD_RED. By only using BLACK and WHITE, we avoid red.\n\nNow let me write the corrected files.",
