        "content": "The user reported that in the web interface the WiFi display doesn't work, settings cannot be opened, and the design should be changed to IBM Carbon style. I already:\n\n1. Read the full index.h to understand the structure and find bugs\n2. Rewrote index.h completely with a clean IBM Carbon-inspired design (light theme, IBM Plex Sans font, proper CSS variables, clean layout)\n3. Fixed WiFi status display: now shows a proper badge with \"Connected\" / \"AP Mode\" text, updates via SSE\n4. Fixed settings modal: openModal() is now attached to window, uses flex display, cancel button works, Save & Reboot button is properly structured\n5. Fixed calibration functions: attached to window so inline onclick works\n6. Built successfully with no errors\n\nThe web interface now has:\n- IBM Carbon-like design (light background, white cards, blue accent #0f62fe, proper typography)\n- Header with title \"Moisture Monitor\" and right side with WiFi badge + Settings button\n- WiFi badge updates in real-time via SSE (shows \"Connected\" green or \"AP Mode\")\n- Settings button opens a clean modal with WiFi SSID/password fields, Cancel and Save & Reboot buttons\n- Modal pre-fills current SSID from /api/wifi endpoint\n- Save sends POST to /api/config/wifi and shows reboot message\n- All calibration buttons (Dry/Wet/Reset) use query parameters as before\n- Sensor name editing works inline\n\nCompilation is successful. Everything should work now.",
