        "content": "**Turns summarized:** 14 | **Compactions so far:** 0\n\n**User Goal:** Build a Plant Moisture Monitor with ESP32-S3, E-Ink display, and web configuration interface.\n\n**What Was Done:**\n- Created Display library using GxEPD2_213_Z98c in black/white mode with setPartialWindow updates only on sensor changes.\n- Developed WebServer with endpoints: /api/status (sensor data), /api/config/wifi (WiFi credentials), /api/config/sensor (sensor names and calibration actions via query parameter ?index=N).\n- Redesigned web front-end in IBM Carbon style: light theme, IBM Plex Sans, card layout, WiFi status badge via SSE, settings modal for WiFi config, inline sensor name editing, calibration buttons.\n- Compiled successfully (pio run -e esp32-s3-devkitc-1).\n\n**Current State:**\n- After compilation, user reports two issues:\n  1. Saving WiFi settings returns \"invalid json\".\n  2. Need ability to remove sensor pins from web GUI (delete sensors).\n- Assistant created a plan to debug WiFi save and add delete sensor functionality, and has begun reading source files.\n\n**Pending / Next Steps:**\n- Debug WiFi save endpoint to fix JSON parsing/handling.\n- Add delete sensor endpoint in backend (likely remove from config file).\n- Update frontend to allow sensor deletion.\n\n**Key Context:**\n- Board: ESP32-S3-DevKitC-1-N8 (8MB Flash, no PSRAM).\n- Framework: PlatformIO with Arduino.\n- Libraries: GxEPD2, Adafruit GFX, ArduinoJson, AsyncWebServer, SPIFFS/LittleFS for config storage.\n- Display SPI pins: CS=8, DC=3, RST=4, BUSY=2 (from earlier code).\n- Web server runs on port 80, serves index.html from PROGMEM.\n- Previously had issues with WiFi display and settings modal not opening; fixed by Carbon redesign.",
