        "tool": "code",
        "command": "Read WebServer.cpp, main.cpp, and index.h fully. Return a summary of the current state of each file, focusing on endpoints (WebServer.cpp), main loop and global initialization (main.cpp), and UI structure (index.h). Do not make any changes.",
        "label": "Updating code",
        "content": "Summary: Summary of files:\n\nWebServer.cpp: Implements an AsyncWebServer on port 80. Provides endpoints: GET / (serves index.html), GET /api/status (returns sensor data in JSON), POST /api/calibrate/dry?index=, POST /api/calibrate/wet?index=, POST /api/calibrate/reset?index=, POST /api/config/sensor?index= (body JSON with name), DELETE /api/sensor?index=, GET /api/calibration, GET /wifi (captive portal form), POST /wifi/connect (logs in, saves creds, reboots), GET /api/wifi, POST /api/config/wifi (JSON body, saves and reboots). Also sets up SSE endpoint /events for real-time status updates. The server handles captive portal DNS in AP mode.\n\nmain.cpp: Global initialization: sets up sensor pins (GPIO6-10), creates Calibration, SensorManager, Display, WebServer objects. In setup(), initializes all modules and shows initial status on display. In loop(), handles serial commands for calibration (c toggles mode, digits select sensor, d/w/r for dry/wet/reset, s to print status), reads sensors every 2 seconds and sends SSE events, updates display every 10 seconds. Also calls webServer.handleClient() to process DNS in AP mode.\n\nindex.h: Contains the entire HTML/CSS/JS for the web UI. It provides a modern, responsive interface with sensor cards (gauge, metrics, name, calibration buttons). Uses SSE (EventSource) to receive real-time status updates and update cards. Includes a settings modal for WiFi configuration. JavaScript functions call the REST API endpoints for calibration, deletion, and WiFi settings.",
