        "content": "## Conversation Summary\n**Turns summarized:** 10  |  **Compactions so far:** 0\n\n### User Goal\nDevelop firmware for WeActStudio 2.13\" tri-color e-ink display (GDEY0213Z98) on ESP32-S3, fix initialization, correct pin mapping, and implement partial updates.\n\n### What Was Done\n- Reviewed official WeActStudio ESP32-S3 example; identified correct pins: CS=10, BUSY=3, RES=46, DC=9 (current project uses CS=5, BUSY=4, RST=16, DC=17).\n- Fixed Display initialization: moved pin definitions to constructor in Display.h, removed redundant arguments from init() calls.\n- Implemented firstPage/nextPage structure in Display.cpp, added showInitial and showPartial methods (not yet integrated).\n- Attempted build; likely failed due to GxEPD2 library version mismatch (3.1.1 vs required 4.0.0+).\n- User requested sensor add/delete to update display without full refresh.\n\n### Current State\n- Display code partially fixed (constructor, init, base methods) but partial update not functional because GxEPD2 library is too old.\n- Build probably broken.\n- No sensor management tied to display updates.\n\n### Pending / Next Steps\n- Update GxEPD2 library to >=4.0.0 in platformio.ini.\n- Fully integrate partial update: use showInitial at startup, showPartial for changes.\n- Implement sensor addition/removal in web UI that calls display update (partial).\n- Verify pin definitions match actual display variant.\n\n### Key Context\n- Board: esp32-s3-devkitc-1, PlatformIO, ESP32-S3.\n- Display: WeActStudio 2.13\" tri-color, driver GxEPD2_213_Z98c.\n- Library: GxEPD2 v3.1.1 (needs upgrade).\n- Pin discrepancy: official example vs current project may cause red background.\n- Language: Russian/English.\n",
