        "content": "## Conversation Summary\n**Turns summarized:** ~12  |  **Compactions so far:** 0\n\n### User Goal\nThe user is developing an ESP32-S3 irrigation controller with e-ink display, adding configurable settings, redesigning the UI to Flipper Zero style, and fixing WiFi settings save.\n\n### What Was Done\n- Created `lib/Settings/Settings.h` and `.cpp` with `displayInterval` and `updatePriority`, stored via Preferences namespace \"settings\", includes `toJson`/`fromJson` methods.\n- Updated WebServer to accept `Settings` pointer; added `GET/POST /api/settings` endpoints; updated index.h with interval/priority fields in modal; modified `main.cpp` to create Settings object.\n- Redesigned Display: replaced fonts with `FreeMonoBold18pt7b` (percentage) and `FreeMonoBold9pt7b` (labels); added 16×13 droplet icon bitmap; layout: top WiFi bar, center percentage + droplet, bottom sensor name/raw value; applied same style to `showCalibrationScreen` and `showMessage`.\n- Fixed WiFi save bug: `/api/config/wifi` POST with JSON caused \"invalid JSON\" due to content-type handling; switched to form-urlencoded; updated frontend form accordingly.\n\n### Current State\nProject compiles successfully for ESP32-S3-DevKitC-1. Display shows moisture percentage in Flipper Zero style. WiFi credentials save/load via web interface works. Settings endpoints are functional.\n\n### Pending / Next Steps\n- None explicitly stated; further refinements may follow.\n\n### Key Context\n- Board: esp32-s3-devkitc-1\n- Libraries: ESPAsyncWebServer, GxEPD2, Preferences, FreeMonoBold fonts\n- Modified files: `lib/Display/Display.h/.cpp`, `lib/Settings/Settings.h/.cpp`, `lib/WebServer/WebServer.h/.cpp`, `lib/WebServer/index.h`, `src/main.cpp`\n- WiFi save uses form-urlencoded to avoid JSON parsing issues with ESPAsyncWebServer.",
