        "label": "Read the following files to understand project ...",
        "content": "Summary: The project is an ESP32-S3-based multi-sensor soil moisture monitor with a web server for configuration. Key findings:\n\n- **Network/Routing**: The web server uses ESPAsyncWebServer. It first tries to connect to a saved WiFi (SSID/password stored in Preferences). If no saved credentials or connection fails, it starts an AP mode with SSID 'Polivator-Config' at IP 192.168.4.1 and runs a DNS server to catch all DNS requests for captive portal. The AP mode serves a WiFi configuration page at /wifi and handles POST /wifi/connect to save credentials. It also provides a REST API at /api/* for sensor data, calibration, settings, etc.\n\n- **HTTP Server Setup**: The AsyncWebServer is instantiated on port 80 in WebServer.h. Routes are set up in WebServer::setupRoutes() including root serving index_html_content (from index.h), /api/status, /api/calibrate/dry, /api/calibrate/wet, /api/calibrate/reset, /api/config/sensor, /api/sensor (DELETE/ENABLE), /api/calibration, /wifi (captive portal), /wifi/connect, /api/wifi, /api/config/wifi, /api/settings, and an event source (SSE) at /events. The server is started after WiFi setup.\n\n- **Flash Size**: Not explicitly defined in platformio.ini. The board 'esp32-s3-devkitc-1' defaults to 16MB flash (esp32-s3 typically uses 16MB or 8MB). The partition scheme is not set; default 'default_16MB.csv' likely applies. Flash mode is QIO.\n\n- **Partition Scheme**: Not specified in platformio.ini, so PlatformIO uses the default partition scheme for the chosen board (esp32-s3-devkitc-1). The default partition table for ESP32-S3 with 16MB flash typically allocates app0 (1.3MB), app1 (1.3MB), spiffs (1.5MB), and other small partitions. No custom partitions are defined.\n\n- **Dependencies**: ESPAsyncWebServer, AsyncTCP, GxEPD2 (display), ArduinoJson.\n\n- **Build Flags**: -DARDUINO_USB_CDC_ON_BOOT=1 enables USB CDC serial, -Ilib adds library include path.\n",
