        "command": "Add OTA firmware update support: modify WebServer.cpp, WebServer.h, and main.cpp.\n\n1. In WebServer.h, add a method declaration for the update handler and a boolean flag for update in progress.\n2. In WebServer.cpp, add a new route `POST /update` that accepts firmware binary upload via the AsyncWebServer's onUpload/onBody callbacks. Use `Update` class to flash the binary and reboot on success.\n3. In main.cpp, add `ArduinoOTA` basics (optional, but useful for background updates).\n\nAlso adjust platformio.ini to ensure partition scheme allows OTA (e.g., add `board_upload.flash = 16MB` and `board_build.partitions = default_16MB.csv` if needed).\n\nRead current WebServer.cpp to plan insertion point for the new route.",
        "label": "Implementing feature",
        "content": "Summary: Add OTA update support: Added handleUpdate method and updateInProgress flag to WebServer.h; included Update.h and added /update route with onUpload handler in WebServer.cpp; added ArduinoOTA include, begin() and handle() calls in main.cpp; added partition scheme and flash size in platformio.ini.\n  ~ lib/WebServer/WebServer.h\n  ~ lib/WebServer/WebServer.cpp\n  ~ lib/WebServer/WebServer.cpp\n  ~ src/main.cpp\n  ~ src/main.cpp\n  ~ src/main.cpp\n  » platformio.ini",
