        "content": "We need to fix the 503 error. The 503 Service Unavailable typically occurs when the server is overloaded or cannot handle requests. Since this is an ESP32 running an async web server, 503 could be due to:\n- Server not fully initialized when request arrives\n- Out of memory\n- WiFi not ready\n- Routes not properly set up\n\nLet's check the WebServer.cpp to see if there are any issues with the server initialization or routes. Also, the user said \"сбились номера пинов\" (pin numbers messed up). Probably after the OTA failure, the pins changed. We need to verify the current pin mapping.\n\nSince the user wants new documentation, we should:\n1. Fix the 503 error\n2. Verify and correct pin assignments\n3. Write updated README.md with correct pinout and troubleshooting\n\nLet's first investigate the 503. We'll read WebServer.cpp and WebServer.h to understand the setup, particularly the init order and whether the server is started before WiFi is ready.\n\nBut the plan says step 1 is done. Now we should proceed with step 2: Analyze 503 error cause. Let's read WebServer.cpp and WebServer.h.",
