        "type": "reasoning",
        "content": "We need to fix the critical bug: `getIndexFromParam` is a local lambda captured by reference in route handlers, but it goes out of scope. We must either make it a static function, a class member, or define it outside `setupRoutes()` (e.g., as a private method).\n\nAlso `updateInProgress` flag can become stuck. Add a timeout reset when upload error or after some time.\n\nAlso need to update pin assignments and documentation.\n\nLet's execute:\n\n1. Fix `getIndexFromParam` – make it a static method or extract to a helper function outside the lambda capture. Since the lambda is captured by reference, we can make it a regular function defined before `setupRoutes` (as static). Or change the lambdas to capture `this` and call a member function. Simpler: define a static function outside `setupRoutes` inside the same scope (but still inside method). Actually we can move the lambda definition to a member function `int getIndexFromParam(AsyncWebServerRequest *request)` and then in routes use `[this](auto req){ this->getIndexFromParam(req); }`. That's safest.\n\n2. Add a static variable or class member to track last update progress and reset flag after timeout.\n\n3. After code fixes, update README with correct pins.\n\nLet's do this in one code call.",
