        "type": "reasoning",
        "content": "The user wants me to analyze the project in swarm mode and identify improvements. The first swarm attempt failed (all tasks after researcher were blocked because they depended on the researcher). I need to re-run the swarm properly. But the user just said \"повтори\" (repeat). Let me redo the swarm with all necessary reads done first, then the analysis tasks. However, I already have the file contents now. I can proceed with analysis directly. But the user asked for swarm mode. Let me run a proper swarm with all tasks having correct dependencies.\n\nActually, I already have the key files read. I can now run the analysis tasks in parallel without dependency on researcher. Let me create a swarm with tasks that directly analyze the code I've already read.\n\nBetter: I'll run a simplified swarm: all analysts read from the files already cached in context. I'll set readOnly:true for their reading tasks but they can just analyze from memory. But the code agent won't have the files in context unless I pass them. Alternatively, I can run a single code agent to read all files and produce a combined analysis. But the user specifically wants swarm mode.\n\nLet me design a proper swarm:\n\n1. researcher: read all files (but I already read them, so this is redundant)\n2. code-reviewer: depends on researcher - analyze code quality\n3. architect: depends on researcher - analyze architecture\n4. security: depends on researcher - analyze security\n5. backend-dev: depends on researcher - analyze performance\n6. synthesizer: depends on 2,3,4,5 - synthesize results\n\nThe problem last time was that the researcher didn't actually produce file contents in a way that downstream agents could use. I need to ensure the researcher's output is accessible. I'll use the temp-store or just have each agent read files themselves (they all have the same capability). That would make them independent and run in parallel.\n\nLet me redesign: all analysis tasks are independent - each reads the files themselves and produces analysis. No dependency on researcher. Then synthesizer depends on all 4 analysts.\n\nThat way they can all run in parallel (maxConcurrency: 4).",
