        "label": "Read lib/WebServer/WebServer.h, lib/WebServer/W...",
        "content": "Summary: The web server structure consists of a main `WebServer` class that manages an ESPAsyncWebServer, DNS server for captive portal, and OTA updates. Key components: \n- `begin()` sets up WiFi (either connect to saved or start AP mode with SSID 'Polivator-Config'), initializes routes.\n- `setupRoutes()` defines all REST API endpoints: `/api/status`, `/api/calibrate/dry`, `/api/calibrate/wet`, `/api/calibrate/reset`, `/api/config/sensor`, `/api/sensor` (DELETE), `/api/sensor/enable`, `/api/calibration`, `/api/wifi`, `/api/config/wifi`, `/api/settings` (GET/POST), `/update` (OTA), and `/wifi` for captive portal configuration. Also serves the main UI from `index_html_content` on `/`.\n- Authentication: There is **no authentication** implemented on any endpoint. All routes are publicly accessible without any login or token requirement. This is a critical security gap.\n- The web UI is embedded in `index.h` as a PROGMEM string (first 30 lines show a dark-themed HTML page with CSS variables).\n- WiFi credentials are stored in `Preferences` (NVS) and can be changed via `/wifi/connect` or `/api/config/wifi`.\n- SSE events are available at `/events` for real-time sensor status updates (`sendStatusEvent`).",
