        "command": "Edit lib/WebServer/WebServer.cpp to add basic HTTP authentication using request->authenticate().\n\n1. In `setupRoutes()`, for every route handler EXCEPT:\n   - `\"/\"` (root GET) - serves UI\n   - `\"/events\"` (SSE) - read-only status\n   - `\"/wifi\"` (GET) - captive portal\n   - `\"/api/wifi\"` (POST) - initial WiFi setup (needs to be open)\n\n   Add the following check at the beginning of the handler lambda:\n   ```cpp\n   if (!request->authenticate(\"admin\", \"admin\")) {\n       request->requestAuthentication();\n       return;\n   }\n   ```\n\n2. Also for the OTA update route (which is registered differently, likely in updateHandler), add the same check.\n\n3. For the `/api/wifi` route, add a check: if there is already a saved SSID in preferences (meaning setup is done), then require auth; otherwise allow open (first-time setup). Use `if (preferences.getString(\"ssid\", \"\").length() > 0) ...`.\n\n4. Add constants at top of file for default auth credentials (username/password) for easy change.\n\nRead the file again to get current state and make precise edits.",
